Hello everyone!
I need some help in Hubl lang. Actually i am trying to add all elements of an array in a variable but unable to do so. Below is a code snippet. I am trying to display sum in email template. This is always giving 0.
Any help will be greatly appreciated. Thanks!

```{% set valuesArray = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5] %}
{% set sum = 0 %}

{% for value in valuesArray %}
   {% set sum = sum + value %}
{% endfor %}

<p>The sum of array elements is: {{ sum }}</p>```

Hi try this: 

{% set valuesArray = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5] %}
{% set sum = 0 %}

{% for value in valuesArray %}
    {% set sum = sum | add(value) %}
{% endfor %}

&lt;p&gt;The sum of array elements is: {{ sum }}&lt;/p&gt;

I think hubl doesn't support direct arithmetic operations try this and let me know: {% set valuesArray = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5] %}
{% set sum = 0 %}

{% for value in valuesArray %}
    {% set sum = sum + value %}
{% endfor %}

&lt;p&gt;The sum of array elements is: {{ sum }}&lt;/p&gt;

{% set valuesArray = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5] %}
{% set sum = valuesArray | sum %}

&lt;p&gt;The sum of array elements is: {{ sum }}&lt;/p&gt;

Try this and if this doesn't work I will try it on my end until it does
